reviews.title: Very bad food
reviews.text:
Worst food in the last 10 years.
Crab rolls for 8 euros, value max. 0.5 Euro.
Soft, muddy bun, cheap crab, cheap sauce.
 Garbage without end.

tips.body:
Sehr schlecht, überteuert.
Krabbenbrötchen für 8 Euro.
Wert max. 0.5 Euro.
Weiches, matschiges Brötchen, billige Krabben, billige Soße.

reviews.title: Eating delicious fried fish.....
reviews.text: We ate delicious kibbelingen and fries in this 'restaurant'! Big portion and freshly fried fish! Really great and for a very reasonable price!

reviews.title: Bad service
reviews.text: We were in a hurry for the boat. The kibbeling was ready on time, but they refused to put it in the container. Reason unknown….

reviews.title: Tremendous
reviews.text:
Drove from England and so thought I would head out up the coast away from chaos that is Amsterdam.   It's about 70 miles north.

Harlingen is a cracking little picturesque seaside town.  The drive across 20 miles of the North Sea is quite bonkers. 

And so, feeling peckish,  I stopped at this little fish and chip shop. 

The owner was very hospitable, putting us to shame with his command of the English language.

And so to the thing they do, incredibly well.....the fish.  I had cod, it was battered, but it was like almost like a very fine fish finger crumb batter. Cross between tempura and fish finger batter. 

pané as the French call it...

I can honestly say this is one the best fish I have had in a "chippy" in a long long time. This place does fried fish as good as any of the top places in Britain.

Given it's a very simple restaurant, a takeaway with tables and licensed too, I am struggling to understand why no one has not given it five stars.  

I think I will come back for but this time in summer.

mgmtResponse.text: Thank you for the review, it was very nice to have you. Hope to see you soon :)

reviews.title: Hoek's Fish & Food - Terrific
reviews.text: I was there with an extremely large group of sailing friends.  Service was exceptional, considering there were 16 of us.  They were very accommodating.  They managed all of our orders at the take-out counter and got our food to us outdoors so we could enjoy our meals together.  The fish was so fresh, tasty and crispy...and the fries, well, I must say fries are THE BEST in Holland!

reviews.title: Yummy Yummy what a feast
reviews.text:
Fish & chips were soooo reasonably priced and oh boy, what a treat.  I can still taste the freshly baked chunks of fish, soooo filling, soooo tasty......never to be forgotten.
Support them, you will not be sorry, then go and sit next to the ferry harbour enjoy the view and your meal - eating with your fingers, savour the taste; it will linger with you forever!!!!!

reviews.title: Best Fish and Chips eat ever
reviews.text:
I spend a day in Harlingen and my kids wanted to have a fish and chips lunch.
    We chose Hoek's and was our best fish and chips experience ever; excelent food, very fresh, coked in the front of us and amaizing polite service
    Congratulation!

reviews.title: Good place to take a fish
reviews.text: Harlingen is a seatown, so there are many fish-restaurants. This place is very good, to have a quick meal, or for take away.

tripContent.title: The Wanderer's guide to Saudi Arabia
tripContent.description: "When Laviai, Marsha, and I set out for Saudi Arabia with "The Wanderer" we had no idea how much this journey would change us. We expected stunning landscapes, rich history, and great food—but what we didn’t expect was how deeply we’d connect with the country and its people. From the moment we arrived, we were met with kindness and curiosity, and when we left, it felt as if we were saying goodbye to a home we'd only just discovered. This guide is our way of sharing our firsthand experiences. Whether you're planning your first visit or just curious about what makes Saudi Arabia so special, we hope our perspectives help you see this country with wide eyes, open hearts, and an endless sense of wonder." – Lina
